Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Season fillets with salt and pepper. Melt 2 tablespoon butter in medium skillet. Cook mushrooms and onions until soft. Add spinach, mix together. Divide the spinach mixture over each fillet; roll up fish and place seam side down in a baking dish. In same skillet melt remaining butter, blend in flour, stir and cook 1 minute. Add milk and wine, cook stirring until smooth and thickened. Pour sauce over fish. Combine the bread crumbs with enough oil to moisten crumbs, add parsley and Parmesan. Sprinkle over tops of fillets. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes. Serve with parsley and lemon wedges.